{
  "text": "Nanotechnology is a promising new field with potential applications in the domestic, industrial, and biomedical fields. [CITATION_1] Due to the growing number of applications, there is an increasing risk to animals from environmental exposure to nanomaterials. Their potential toxicologic impact is still under investigation and our actual knowledge about the effects of nanosized contaminants on biological systems remains incomplete. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] These effects need to be assessed in order to provide a scientific basis for safe development of nanotechnologies. Use of nanotechnology has seen exponential growth in the areas of health care, consumer products, clothes, electronics, and sporting goods. [CITATION_4] This is due to the unique chemical, mechanical, optical, magnetic, and biological properties of nanomaterials that make them desirable for commercial and medical applications.",
